articles.author: Jack Kim
articles.description: South Korea's President Yoon Suk Yeol faces a new and potentially more robust attempt to arrest him on insurrection charges after a top investigator vowed to do whatever it takes to break a security blockade and take in the impeached leader.
articles.title: South Korea's Yoon faces second arrest attempt in fortified compound

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: More than 400 people trapped by a strong earthquake that struck the foothills of the Himalayas on Tuesday have been rescued, Chinese authorities said, while over 30,000 residents have been relocated, as rescuers continue the search for survivors.
articles.title: Rescue efforts under way after earthquake in Tibet kills more than 120

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israeli military strikes across Gaza killed at least 22 people on Wednesday, Palestinian medics said, as the U.S. stepped up efforts to overcome sticking points between Israel and Hamas to reach a ceasefire to end the war.
articles.title: Israeli strikes kill dozens in Gaza as US pushes for ceasefire

articles.author: Steve Holland, Joseph Ax
articles.description: U.S. President-elect Donald Trump refused on Tuesday to rule out using military or economic action to pursue acquisition of the Panama Canal and Greenland, part of a broader expansionist agenda he has promoted since winning the Nov. 5 election.
articles.title: Trump will not rule out force to take Panama Canal, Greenland

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Finland's public transport agency said on Wednesday that an oil tanker suspected of damaging undersea cables in the Baltic Sea has been found to have serious deficiencies and will not be allowed to operate until repairs have been made.
articles.title: Finland says oil tanker linked to subsea cable damage has serious deficiencies

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Austrian Foreign Minister Alexander Schallenberg will be named caretaker chancellor later on Wednesday, Austrian media reported, taking over from Karl Nehammer, who quit when centrist coalition talks collapsed over the weekend.
articles.title: Austrian foreign minister to become caretaker chancellor, reports say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Greenland's leader will meet the Danish king in Copenhagen on Wednesday, after U.S. President-elect Donald Trump said he wanted to take control of the Arctic island, an autonomous territory of Denmark.
articles.title: Greenland leader to meet Danish king amid Trump bid to take over territory

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: German opposition leader Friedrich Merz, tipped to become chancellor in next month's election, said Germany would spend more on defence but would not commit to a NATO defence spending target as called for by U.S. President-elect Donald Trump.
articles.title: Germany's front-runner for chancellor won't commit to new NATO spending target

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ukrainian drones struck deep inside Russia overnight and attacked the Saratov region, causing a major fire in the city of Engels, the local governor said on Wednesday.
articles.title: Ukraine stages drone attack on Russia's Saratov region, causing big fire

articles.author: Camillus Eboh
articles.description: The Nigerian military said on Wednesday its troops had killed 34 Islamist militants in a gun battle in northeastern Borno state and six soldiers had also died.
articles.title: Nigerian troops repel Boko Haram ambush in Borno, kill 34 insurgents
